Strings 


string = "a string of characters inside quotation marks" 


len(string)            < Will find the length of string
print(len(string))     < Will print the result. 


Indexing: 
string[0]       < Returns value of [index] 
string[-1]      <                           This counts backwards from [0]

Slicing: 
string[x:y]    > Returns new string snipped from index X to Y. 
string[x:]     > Returns new string starting from X to ...end of string
string[:y]     > Returns new string starting from ...start of string to Y
string[:]      > Returns new string - Exact copy of orginonal. 

Functions: 
len()       < Find the length of a string


